Image supplied: The Perdeberg Pinotage and Biltong Festival is returning for 2022The event, which takes place over the weekend of 23 and 24 April, promises to be a fun day for everyone. Situated at the foothills of the Paardeberg Mountain in Paarl, this weekend is the perfect excuse to escape the hustle and bustle of the city. Attendees will be able to sample Pinotage paired with a range of biltong products and experience Perdeberg’s Endura Winemaker’s Selection Cape Red - which is not usually available for tasting. Tang opens doors in Cape Town2 days ago Another gem from the Perdeberg range not to miss out on is the Dry Land Collection Resolve Pinotage. On the nose, this wine shows a distinctive spiciness with undertones of fresh cherries and strawberry cordial.  These two wines, together with other wines in their portfolio as well their craft beer range and bubbly will be available throughout the weekend’s festivities. For those familiar with the Pinotage and Biltong Festival, it will be no surprise that there are another 17 wine cellars participating in the festival. This affords you the unique opportunity to taste the wines of a number of wine regions all in one place! Each wine is paired with a specific kind of biltong to highlight the wine’s attributes. Image supplied: Festival goers go for the Pinotage and Biltong Festival dress codeDo not forget to don your Purple and White outfits to blend in with the atmosphere… Choose from three ticket options being the Regular Tickets (R300 per person), VIP Tickets (R550 per person) or the Dedicated Driver Ticket (R200 per person). For more details on the ticket options as well as bookings (pre-booking is essential) go here.